                  <decoDesc>
                     <decoNote type="drawing" xml:id="d1">
                        <locus target="#1r"/>

                        <desc>Drawing is made with ink, and is partly colored.
                          Emperor <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS7006Menilek">
                          Mǝnilǝk II</persName> riding on the horse,
                          accompanied by servants and soldiers with guns and banners.
                          The legend in the bottom right corner reads

                          <foreign xml:lang="am">ጃንሆይ፡ ያንድ፡ ቀን፡ አይን፡ ነውና፡ እንዳይነውርብኝ፡
                          የየካቲት፡ ጊወርጊስን፡ ያነገሱለት፡ አይቼ፡ ዛሬ፡ ሰራሁት፡ </foreign>
                        <foreign xml:lang="en">Your Majesty, this is an impression of one day; may it
                          not become a shame for me.
                          Today I have made (a picture of) what
                          I saw when you enthroned (the <foreign>tābot</foreign>
                          of) <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS4585Georgeo">George</persName> in <date>Yakkātit</date>.
                        </foreign>
                          </desc>
                        <note>The drawing refers to <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS7006Menilek">
                          Mǝnilǝk II</persName> attending the feast of introducing
                          a <persName type="tabot" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS4585Georgeo">George of Lydda</persName>
                          into a new church ("enthroning of the tābot"), that probably took place
                          at <placeName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LOC3292Gannat">Gannata Ṣǝge Giyorgis</placeName>
                           on the Saint's monthly celebration on <date>23 Yakkātit (= 2 March)</date>,
                           after 1896 but before 1900. A Russian
                         translation of the legend included into <bibl corresp="http://zotero.org/groups/358366/items/T6UTP6JE"><seg type="book"><!-- attributes from original bibl--></seg><ptr target="bm:Turaev1906rukopisi"/><title level="m">Ėfiopskija rukopisi v S.-Peterburgě</title><title level="s">Pamjatniki ėfiopskoj pis'mennosti</title><author><t:forename xmlns:t="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">Boris</t:forename><t:surname xmlns:t="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">Turaev</t:surname></author><pubPlace>Sanktpeterburg</pubPlace><publisher>Tipografija imperatorskoj Akademii Nauk</publisher><date>1906</date><series><t:title xmlns:t="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" level="s">Pamjatniki ėfiopskoj pis'mennosti</t:title><t:biblScope xmlns:t="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" unit="volume">3</t:biblScope></series><biblScope unit="volume">3</biblScope><note type="url">http://digitale-sammlungen.ulb.uni-bonn.de/content/titleinfo/2104581</note><citedRange unit="page">32</citedRange></bibl>.
                       </note>
                        </decoNote>

